// NOTE on the 5 "_impl" renames below (標準作業/五回なぜ/受領証/価値流/工程能力): the
// real reference crate (豊田コード生産方式_v26.7.19) declares `#[path="X.rs"] pub mod X;`
// for a module whose own file ALSO defines `pub struct X { .. }` -- an explicit item
// always shadows a glob import of the same identifier in Rust, so `X { .. }` /
// `X::新規()` calls in 試験.rs resolve to the *module* instead of the *struct*,
// which fails to compile (E0425/E0573/E0574). The reference's own 公開記録.json
// discloses this: "立脚点: 構造検査合格・コンパイル未確認" (structural inspection passed,
// compilation NOT verified) -- this is a genuine defect in the shipped reference, not
// a generation bug. Fix, scoped to internal wiring only (zero effect on the public
// API 試験.rs exercises): declare the mod under a mangled identifier and re-export
// the real type under its real name via `pub use`, so top-level `X` resolves to the
// struct only. 試験.rs is unmodified.
